{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_207","type":"agent_message","text":"The MyBatis logger failure is clearer now: `LogFactory` initializes logging implementations via reflective constructor lookup, and if none of those constructors are registered it silently leaves `logConstructor` null. I’m patching that path directly, along with the missing Boot `ApplicationListener` classes from `spring.factories`, before rerunning the native test."}}
